body: Which of the following statements about triangles is not correct?

choices.W: The sum of the exterior angles is twice the sum of the interior angles of the triangles
choices.X: The circumradius must be greater than or equal to twice the inradius
choices.Y: Drawing the medians of each side of a triangle splits the triangle into 6 equal areas

answer: Z) The area of a triangle is equal to the inradius times the perimeter of the triangle
